{
  "text": "The combination of several minimally invasive methods of treatment, allowing multiple access to necrotic collection, is an optimal strategy for the treatment of WOPN [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Widening of the access to necrotic areas provides better draining conditions and increases the efficiency of treatment [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . The method of access to WOPN should depend not only on the location of necrosis but also on the experience of the medical center.",
